Thanks so much to @artsy & @dblockdotorg for enlightening AppNexus EngAtScale with how & why to build a test-driven culture. #liveatappnexus
"How to maintain a test-driven culture: #4 Use a crappier, non-compiling language. Do DevOps." -@dblockdotorg [We happen to agree =) ]
#2 Hire from open source projects. #3 Remove the safety net. No "worked on my machine; now it's an ops problem"@dblockdotorg #liveatappnexus
How to maintain a test-driven culture: #1. Remove those who talk about testing. Promote those who are testing. @dblockdotorg #liveatappnexus
We have some projects that have 5000 tests and they take 5 seconds to run. -@dblockdotorg #liveatappnexus
As you grow, break things apart. Test individual components as well as the integration. -@dblockdotorg #liveatappnexus
You have to build something that is sustainable. If your tests are reliable, you can scale the company. -@dblockdotorg #liveatappnexus

Why test? Well, what is the cost of failure: Demo in front of investor? 
VIP using our site? 100ks of users? Selling things? -@dblockdotorg
#2: Take a common bug and make it a test. This becomes a fix. - @dblockdotorg #liveatappnexus
"How to build a test-driven culture. #1: Make testing second nature." -@dblockdotorg #liveatappnexus
One of the wins for @artsy was doing javascript testing. We started w/ Jasmine, & now use Node, Mocha, Sinon, JSDom, Zombie." @dblockdotorg
